benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to invoice item

covered: Valid PUT request scenarios with proper payload (TC01, TC02, TC03)
Very large payload / payload size handling (TC12)
SQL injection attempt handling in field values (TC14)
gaps: Partial Update handling is not explicitly tested (are partial updates allowed or rejected?)
Explicit concurrency/race-condition scenarios are not clearly covered beyond idempotency (e.g., two writers updating same item simultaneously)
Pagination handling is not tested (PUT generally operates on a single resource, but large datasets may be relevant for parallel/integration tests)
Caching behavior / ETag handling is not tested
Rate limiting / throttling tests are not present
Detailed 4xx/5xx response body validation beyond generic messages is limited
recommendations: Add a dedicated Partial Update vs. full replace test to confirm API semantics for updates (reject or allow) and validate specific fields affected
Introduce explicit concurrency/race-condition tests (two parallel updates to the same invoice item) to verify isolation and consistency
Add pagination-related tests if API surface expands to list-like behavior; otherwise document rationale if PUT remains single-resource
Add tests for caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) where applicable to validate client-side caching behavior
Add rate-limiting/throttling tests (e.g., rapid repeated requests) and 429 handling
Enhance 4xx/5xx response body validation to assert precise error structures and codes
